nano does not use the Shift key in shortcuts. 
All shortcuts use lowercase letters and unmodified number keys, so Ctrl+G is NOT Ctrl+Shift+G.

ctrl+g to bring up help

"Meta key" = ALT (usually)

^space - move forward a word
M-space - move backwards a word

^^ (ctrl+6) marks text for cutting
M-^ copy
^K cut (Kut) - if no text marked this will cut a while line
^U paste (uncut)

M-L enables word wrap

